  "metadata": {
    "name": "Resolve information before writing to audit logs",
    "description": "To configure Audit daemon to resolve all uid, gid, syscall,\narchitecture, and socket address information before writing the\nevents to disk, set <tt>log_format</tt> to <tt>ENRICHED</tt>\nin <tt>/etc/audit/auditd.conf</tt>.",
    "rationale": "If option <tt>log_format</tt> isn't set to <tt>ENRICHED</tt>, the\naudit records will be stored in a format exactly as the kernel sends them.",
